{
  "texts": [
    "Another recent exact score-based algorithm called CPBayes (Van Beek and Hoffman 2015) adopts the constraint programming paradigm.",
    "In this paradigm, constraints are defined across the variables and a domain of possible values maintained for each variable.",
    "Note that these are not conditional independence constraints, and so this approach should not be confused with the constraint-based structure learning described in Sect. 2.",
    "As the algorithm explores possible solutions by changing one variable, the constraints mean that the possible values of other variables are altered; a process known as constraint propagation.",
    "A simple application of constraint programming to the Sudoko game may serve to illustrate the concept."
  ]
}